## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Fixed DB path — CLI was creating an empty DB at `~/.skrptiq/skrptiq.db` instead of reading the desktop app's shared DB at `~/Library/Application Support/skrptiq/data/skrptiq.db`.

- `DefaultDBPath` now checks the macOS app location first, falls back to `~/.skrptiq/`
- Startup shows the connected DB path so the user can verify
- Engine errors are shown instead of silently swallowed

### Impact
All slash commands now return real data: 161 nodes, 11 hub imports, 8 profiles from the shared DB. Autocomplete shows actual workflow/node/profile names.

### Note for cross-platform
The macOS `~/Library/Application Support/` path is hardcoded. Will need Linux/Windows equivalents when we ship cross-platform.

### Tests
- `go test ./...` — all passing
- `go vet ./...` — clean
